{
  "id": "2023-06-28_screen_english",
  "date": "2023-06-28",
  "corner": "screen_english",
  "corner_label": "Screen English",
  "title": "",
  "movie": "리틀 이탈리아 (Little Italy)",
  "duration_sec": 850.64,
  "audio_url": "https://rtyzdyyfahddqshgyjvn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/gmp-audio/2023-06-28_screen_english.mp3",
  "script": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 2.74,
      "text": "월간 굿모닝 팝 3개월 구독권 보내드릴게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 3.79,
      "end": 7.87,
      "text": "피곤한 GMP의 에너지를 가득 충전해드릴 이벤트"
    },
    {
      "start": 7.87,
      "end": 9.73,
      "text": "GMP로 영어실력 업!"
    },
    {
      "start": 10.07,
      "end": 10.91,
      "text": "에너지도 업!"
    },
    {
      "start": 11.59,
      "end": 15.93,
      "text": "오늘은 시원 달콤한 콘 아이스크림 모바일 쿠폰 준비했어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 15.93,
      "end": 18.41,
      "text": "신청 메시지 보내주신 분들 중에서"
    },
    {
      "start": 18.41,
      "end": 20.57,
      "text": "5분 뽑아서 보내드릴게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 21.29,
      "end": 24.21,
      "text": "단문 50원과 장문 100원의 추가요금이 부과되는"
    },
    {
      "start": 24.21,
      "end": 28.49,
      "text": "문자 샵 8910 아니면 샵 1061로 신청하시거나"
    },
    {
      "start": 28.49,
      "end": 31.39,
      "text": "무료인 콩 또는 마이케이로 참여해주세요."
    },
    {
      "start": 40.85,
      "end": 61.16,
      "text": "영어가 즐거워지는 영어 놀이터"
    },
    {
      "start": 61.16,
      "end": 64.66,
      "text": "6월에 함께하고 있는 영화는"
    },
    {
      "start": 64.66,
      "end": 68.74,
      "text": "죽기 전에 한 번쯤 맛보고 싶은 맛있는 사랑이야기"
    },
    {
      "start": 68.74,
      "end": 74.12,
      "text": "이렇게 러블리하게 시작을 해봤습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 74.12,
      "end": 77.28,
      "text": "주니퍼 님께서"
    },
    {
      "start": 77.28,
      "end": 80.84,
      "text": "크쌤 오늘도 친근하게 반갑습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 81.9,
      "end": 82.78,
      "text": "주니퍼?"
    },
    {
      "start": 82.78,
      "end": 83.14,
      "text": "펄?"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.3,
      "end": 83.52,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 83.9,
      "end": 84.22,
      "text": "펄?"
    },
    {
      "start": 84.46,
      "end": 85.18,
      "text": "P-E-R"
    },
    {
      "start": 85.18,
      "end": 86.92,
      "text": "진주라고 들어서"
    },
    {
      "start": 86.92,
      "end": 87.34,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 87.72,
      "end": 89.02,
      "text": "발음이 좀 비슷하기는 했네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 89.12,
      "end": 90.04,
      "text": "아, you are a pearl."
    },
    {
      "start": 90.6,
      "end": 91.16,
      "text": "잘할게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 91.28,
      "end": 91.84,
      "text": "열심히 할게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 91.84,
      "end": 92.16,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 92.32,
      "end": 93.72,
      "text": "갑자기 진주가 되셨네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 93.8,
      "end": 94.84,
      "text": "주니퍼 님 환영합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 95.56,
      "end": 96.68,
      "text": "아, 진흙 속의 진주."
    },
    {
      "start": 97.86,
      "end": 98.04,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 98.16,
      "end": 100.78,
      "text": "Anyway, it's very great to see you."
    },
    {
      "start": 100.88,
      "end": 102.32,
      "text": "It's great to see you as always."
    },
    {
      "start": 102.32,
      "end": 102.72,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 103.34,
      "end": 108.72,
      "text": "자, 이제 아무래도 이 영화 속에서 계속해서 피자 가게가 나오다 보니까"
    },
    {
      "start": 108.72,
      "end": 112.16,
      "text": "저는 while watching this movie를 보면서"
    },
    {
      "start": 112.16,
      "end": 115.64,
      "text": "계속해서 I feel like I smell something tasty."
    },
    {
      "start": 115.84,
      "end": 117.22,
      "text": "Something like pizza?"
    },
    {
      "start": 117.34,
      "end": 118.34,
      "text": "tomato sauce?"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.44,
      "end": 118.8,
      "text": "Cheese?"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.94,
      "end": 119.16,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 119.38,
      "end": 121.42,
      "text": "I have been thinking about pizza too."
    },
    {
      "start": 121.52,
      "end": 121.82,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 121.82,
      "end": 124.02,
      "text": "I went to San Francisco recently."
    },
    {
      "start": 124.14,
      "end": 124.5,
      "text": "Oh."
    },
    {
      "start": 124.58,
      "end": 127.04,
      "text": "And I went to the most famous pizza parlor."
    },
    {
      "start": 127.58,
      "end": 128.18,
      "text": "Tony's."
    },
    {
      "start": 128.2,
      "end": 128.9,
      "text": "Who was it?"
    },
    {
      "start": 129.48,
      "end": 130.04,
      "text": "Tony's."
    },
    {
      "start": 130.04,
      "end": 131.52,
      "text": "He's an Italian man."
    },
    {
      "start": 131.6,
      "end": 131.8,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 132.06,
      "end": 133.76,
      "text": "And he immigrated to SF."
    },
    {
      "start": 133.86,
      "end": 134.12,
      "text": "Oh."
    },
    {
      "start": 134.24,
      "end": 135.88,
      "text": "He made a pie, a pizza pie."
    },
    {
      "start": 136.0,
      "end": 136.32,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 136.46,
      "end": 137.56,
      "text": "Absolutely delicious."
    },
    {
      "start": 137.86,
      "end": 139.74,
      "text": "그냥 피자가 아니고 피자 파이에요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 139.94,
      "end": 140.82,
      "text": "They call it pie."
    },
    {
      "start": 140.98,
      "end": 144.48,
      "text": "The more authentic places, they're like one pie, two pies."
    },
    {
      "start": 144.6,
      "end": 144.72,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 144.84,
      "end": 145.54,
      "text": "Italian style."
    },
    {
      "start": 145.98,
      "end": 148.54,
      "text": "Americans just say one pizza, two pizzas."
    },
    {
      "start": 148.64,
      "end": 150.52,
      "text": "거기서 two pies, one pie."
    },
    {
      "start": 150.52,
      "end": 157.62,
      "text": "오, 문화 차이도 미국에서, 이탈리아의 그런 피자 문화에 대해서도 배울 수가 있으셨네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 157.62,
      "end": 157.94,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 158.2,
      "end": 160.56,
      "text": "원래 그 피자 뜻이 이탈리아말로 pie이래요."
    },
    {
      "start": 160.76,
      "end": 161.5,
      "text": "아, 그렇구나."
    },
    {
      "start": 161.52,
      "end": 164.42,
      "text": "But in the U.S., a pie is like a dessert."
    },
    {
      "start": 164.58,
      "end": 164.82,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 164.94,
      "end": 166.74,
      "text": "Like 호박, 단호박 파이."
    },
    {
      "start": 166.74,
      "end": 167.14,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 167.14,
      "end": 167.98,
      "text": "엄청 달달하고."
    },
    {
      "start": 168.14,
      "end": 168.18,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 168.3,
      "end": 169.22,
      "text": "중숙하면서 짤끈하고."
    },
    {
      "start": 169.38,
      "end": 172.18,
      "text": "두께도 뭔가 좀 더 thicker 할 것 같고."
    },
    {
      "start": 172.36,
      "end": 172.64,
      "text": "그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 172.96,
      "end": 173.26,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 173.62,
      "end": 174.18,
      "text": "그렇군요."
    },
    {
      "start": 174.22,
      "end": 175.3,
      "text": "It's much different."
    },
    {
      "start": 176.62,
      "end": 177.06,
      "text": "Anyway."
    },
    {
      "start": 177.06,
      "end": 181.48,
      "text": "근데 이 피자가 was first made in Italy, 맞나요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 181.7,
      "end": 182.3,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 182.6,
      "end": 189.14,
      "text": "There are many different, people say different things, but apparently it was invented in Italy."
    },
    {
      "start": 189.3,
      "end": 196.06,
      "text": "In one region of Italy, where Naples is, the city of Naples, and back then it was a very"
    },
    {
      "start": 196.06,
      "end": 203.12,
      "text": "crowded city near the water, and many people worked outside in tough conditions, so they"
    },
    {
      "start": 203.12,
      "end": 209.0,
      "text": "needed something easy and convenient to eat, so they took some bread, like pocaccia"
    },
    {
      "start": 209.0,
      "end": 214.68,
      "text": "bread, and they put some olive oil and some sauce on it, and that was the start of"
    },
    {
      "start": 214.68,
      "end": 221.34,
      "text": "pizza, but it was not considered a good food, and the upper class, they looked down on it."
    },
    {
      "start": 221.34,
      "end": 225.56,
      "text": "They said, oh, pizza, that's just a poor man's street food."
    },
    {
      "start": 225.9,
      "end": 226.8,
      "text": "이렇게 무시했어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 226.88,
      "end": 227.2,
      "text": "어머."
    },
    {
      "start": 227.22,
      "end": 227.88,
      "text": "거기, 이탈리아."
    },
    {
      "start": 228.04,
      "end": 229.14,
      "text": "원조언대 무시했어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 229.14,
      "end": 234.56,
      "text": "와, 이렇게 the history of pizza에 대해서 들어보니까 또 굉장히 흥미롭네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 234.68,
      "end": 235.68,
      "text": "Invented in Italy."
    },
    {
      "start": 235.82,
      "end": 236.06,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 236.18,
      "end": 239.78,
      "text": "But Americans, us Americans, we made it famous."
    },
    {
      "start": 240.04,
      "end": 241.4,
      "text": "We loved pizza."
    },
    {
      "start": 242.26,
      "end": 245.78,
      "text": "뭔가 표정의 자부심이 한껏 느껴지십니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 245.96,
      "end": 251.56,
      "text": "Many Italians, they emigrated to the U.S. and they started selling pizza."
    },
    {
      "start": 251.56,
      "end": 257.56,
      "text": "On the streets, and then in New York, the first pizza parlor was opened, and it's still"
    },
    {
      "start": 257.56,
      "end": 258.24,
      "text": "there today."
    },
    {
      "start": 258.36,
      "end": 260.24,
      "text": "It was opened back in 1905."
    },
    {
      "start": 260.4,
      "end": 268.1,
      "text": "It's still in Little Italy, in New York City, and pizza became super popular all over the country."
    },
    {
      "start": 268.1,
      "end": 273.58,
      "text": "와, 이렇게 뉴욕 시리를 가게 되면 Little Italy라는 곳을 방문해서 정말"
    },
    {
      "start": 273.58,
      "end": 276.3,
      "text": "피자의 참맛을 느껴보고 싶습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 276.3,
      "end": 278.36,
      "text": "Lombardi's 이란 곳인데요."
    },
    {
      "start": 278.42,
      "end": 278.8,
      "text": "아, 그래요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 278.9,
      "end": 279.62,
      "text": "Lombardi's."
    },
    {
      "start": 279.68,
      "end": 281.14,
      "text": "아주 유명한 곳이군요."
    },
    {
      "start": 281.16,
      "end": 281.92,
      "text": "Very Italian."
    },
    {
      "start": 282.38,
      "end": 285.52,
      "text": "When I was living in New York for a year, I tried all the pizza places."
    },
    {
      "start": 286.42,
      "end": 288.28,
      "text": "My favorite was a different one."
    },
    {
      "start": 288.76,
      "end": 289.7,
      "text": "Anyway, John's pizza."
    },
    {
      "start": 289.7,
      "end": 292.24,
      "text": "Greenwich Village 가면 정말 맛있어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 292.5,
      "end": 295.74,
      "text": "아주 이렇게 정확한 정보들 추가를 해주셨고요."
    },
    {
      "start": 297.0,
      "end": 302.14,
      "text": "이렇게 해서 이제 피자가 결국 미국으로 넘어가면서 훨씬 더"
    },
    {
      "start": 302.14,
      "end": 306.62,
      "text": "It's known over the world 하게 되었다라는 이야기도 해주셨습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 306.62,
      "end": 311.28,
      "text": "Yeah, before the 1940s, 1940년 그 전에."
    },
    {
      "start": 311.76,
      "end": 313.48,
      "text": "It was not even famous in Italy."
    },
    {
      "start": 313.74,
      "end": 315.3,
      "text": "It was only famous in the U.S."
    },
    {
      "start": 315.3,
      "end": 319.9,
      "text": "미국의 영향력에 대해서 한 번 더 어필을 해주셨고요."
    },
    {
      "start": 320.0,
      "end": 320.6,
      "text": "We like pizza."
    },
    {
      "start": 320.78,
      "end": 321.5,
      "text": "We like street food."
    },
    {
      "start": 321.68,
      "end": 322.16,
      "text": "그럼요."
    },
    {
      "start": 322.18,
      "end": 322.76,
      "text": "Common food."
    },
    {
      "start": 322.84,
      "end": 327.62,
      "text": "네, 굉장히 효과적이고 효율적으로 먹을 수 있는 그런 식품이 아닌가 싶습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 327.72,
      "end": 331.18,
      "text": "Bread, cheese, it's got all the calories, all the fat."
    },
    {
      "start": 331.32,
      "end": 332.1,
      "text": "그게 문제네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 333.0,
      "end": 333.64,
      "text": "Nutrients."
    },
    {
      "start": 334.14,
      "end": 335.18,
      "text": "야채 위에 뿌리면."
    },
    {
      "start": 335.28,
      "end": 335.58,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 335.96,
      "end": 336.8,
      "text": "Vegetables."
    },
    {
      "start": 337.16,
      "end": 341.28,
      "text": "채소들을 아주 듬뿍 올리면 괜찮다라는 조언도 해드리면서"
    },
    {
      "start": 341.28,
      "end": 343.04,
      "text": "그럼 오늘 장면 듣고 오시죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 343.04,
      "end": 349.68,
      "text": "I've changed and I'm not afraid to tell you that I'm in love with you."
    },
    {
      "start": 350.5,
      "end": 351.44,
      "text": "I always have been."
    },
    {
      "start": 352.61,
      "end": 353.75,
      "text": "I always will be."
    },
    {
      "start": 354.53,
      "end": 358.09,
      "text": "I'm not afraid to tell my father that I want to start my own shop."
    },
    {
      "start": 358.37,
      "end": 358.55,
      "text": "What?"
    },
    {
      "start": 359.05,
      "end": 360.37,
      "text": "It's about time."
    },
    {
      "start": 360.77,
      "end": 366.19,
      "text": "All this time you never said anything and now that I'm about to get on a plane you"
    },
    {
      "start": 366.19,
      "end": 368.01,
      "text": "finally find the words."
    },
    {
      "start": 368.45,
      "end": 371.24,
      "text": "Love isn't words, it's actions."
    },
    {
      "start": 372.59,
      "end": 372.89,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "start": 373.07,
      "end": 374.55,
      "text": "That's why you let me win today."
    },
    {
      "start": 374.55,
      "end": 378.56,
      "text": "음, 바로 이 장면이었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 378.64,
      "end": 380.12,
      "text": "Oh, the airport."
    },
    {
      "start": 380.58,
      "end": 382.46,
      "text": "Yeah, I burst out crying."
    },
    {
      "start": 382.66,
      "end": 384.26,
      "text": "Oh, you're full of tears."
    },
    {
      "start": 384.42,
      "end": 385.78,
      "text": "아주 눈물이 풍부하네."
    },
    {
      "start": 386.02,
      "end": 386.78,
      "text": "그러니까요."
    },
    {
      "start": 386.98,
      "end": 388.7,
      "text": "왜냐하면 I fell for Nikki."
    },
    {
      "start": 389.7,
      "end": 396.3,
      "text": "이 여성, 이 배우의 입장에 충분히 이제 이입을 하다 보니까 울 수밖에 없었습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 396.3,
      "end": 399.9,
      "text": "She's in the middle of security, airport security."
    },
    {
      "start": 400.02,
      "end": 400.34,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 400.5,
      "end": 402.38,
